ogen planes will only be as sustainable as the energy that powers them,&rdquo; said Carlos L&oacute;pez de la Osa, aviation manager with green group Transport &amp; Environment (T&amp;E)."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;Most hydrogen for transportation is not zero emission today. It&rsquo;s not green hydrogen,&rdquo; said Val Miftakhov, CEO of ZeroAvia, a British-American manufacturer that aims to deliver its <a href=\\"https://zeroavia.com/products-services/\\">first hydrogen-electric aircraft with 40 to 80 seats by 2027</a>."},{"tag":"h2","type":"heading","attributes":{},"content":"2. Hydrogen could cut aircraft range"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Hydrogen is the lightest element, but it has a much lower energy density than kerosene, meaning aircraft powered by it instead of fossil fuels would actually weigh more."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"It can be burned with oxygen to create water, powering a jet, but it has to be stored in liquid form, which means installing high-pressure tanks that keep the highly flammable substance at temperatures below minus 253 Celsius. All that adds weight, cutting into range, cargo and passenger capacity."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Hydrogen can also be used to power a fuel cell, generating electricity to turn a propeller."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"According to a <a href=\\"https://www.mckinsey.com/industries/aerospace-and-defense/our-insights/decarbonizing-the-aviation-sector-making-net-zero-aviation-possible\\">2022 McKinsey study</a>, &ldquo;with current aircraft designs, hydrogen aircraft could be range limited to up to 2,500 kilometers,&rdquo; which is the distance between London and Istanbul. Only &ldquo;redesigning airframes and storage technology might unlock longer ranges without reducing the number of available seats.&rdquo;"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Destination 2050 &mdash; the European aviation alliance for creating net-zero air transport by midcentury, which brings together airlines, airports, manufacturers and navigation service providers &mdash; <a href=\\"https://www.destination2050.eu/four-focus-areas/\\">predicts that hydrogen-powered aircraft</a> will be available by 2035, but only &ldquo;suitable for short-range intra-European routes.&rdquo;"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"That means they can&rsquo;t be used for long-haul flights which <a href=\\"https://www.eurocontrol.int/publication/eurocontrol-think-paper-21-long-haul-flight-decarbonisation-when-can-cutting-edge\\">Eurocontrol</a>, the European air traffic management body, says are responsible for more than 50 percent of aviation&rsquo;s CO2 emissions."},{"tag":"h2","type":"heading","attributes":{},"content":"3. It&rsquo;s going to be expensive"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Today&rsquo;s airports have been set up to refuel airplanes with fossil fuels; they&rsquo;d have to be revamped to supply hydrogen instead."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;There&rsquo;s no hydrogen at the airports today,&rdquo; said Miftakhov. He&rsquo;s convinced the solution will be to &ldquo;make hydrogen on site, at the airports,&rdquo; which will reduce transport costs."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"In January, the California Energy Commission, the state&rsquo;s energy policy agency, <a href=\\"https://www.greencarcongress.com/2024/01/20240123-za.html\\">awarded close to $3.3 million</a> to ZeroAvia to develop a mobile liquid-hydrogen refueling truck that will refuel planes alongside kerosene at the Livermore Municipal Airport."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"However, the scale of the challenge is daunting."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t know the full potential of hydrogen in aviation yet, and there are still significant challenges on the road to make it not only technically but also economically feasible,&rdquo; said Francisco Jos&eacute; Lucas, head of sustainable aviation at the Spanish energy multinational Repsol, referring to the difficulties of getting hydrogen to airports. &ldquo;Nonetheless, we are sure that it is a technology with great potential in the medium and long term.&rdquo;"},{"tag":"h2","type":"heading","attributes":{},"content":"4. Red tape will be a problem"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Aviation arguably has the toughest safety standards of any industry on the planet. That means switching to hydrogen will face very high regulatory hurdles."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;For aircraft with less than 20 passengers, the rules are performance based, and therefore would not require any adaptation&rdquo; to hydrogen propulsion, said Janet Northcote, spokesperson for the EU Aviation Safety Agency (EASA)."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"But, &ldquo;for larger transport aircraft, the regulations are more prescriptive and these would not be appropriate for all aspects in their current form,&rdquo; she said."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"The agency does have something called a Special Condition, which allows for novel technologies and has been used for the Airbus A321XLR &mdash; an extra-long range airplane still <a href=\\"https://www.airbus.com/en/join-us-on-our-a321xlr-journey\\">awaiting certification</a>."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"But in the case of the XLR, that Special Condition applies to a new design for a central fuel tank, not for a novel way of powering flight."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Northcote said EASA is in touch with hydrogen plane developers through the agency&rsquo;s pre-application services."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;The pre-application process helps them de-risk their projects and allows us to identify where current regulations may need to evolve,&rdquo; she said."},{"tag":"h2","type":"heading","attributes":{},"content":"5. Non-CO2 impact"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"After all the effort to convert airplanes from kerosene to hydrogen, even such green machines could still have a negative climate impact."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"Recent <a href=\\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/14693062.2021.1950602\\">studies show</a> that about 50 percent to 75 percent of aviation&rsquo;s climate impact is caused by non-CO2 effects &mdash; such as nitrogen oxide emissions or water vapor &mdash; that contribute to the formation of contrails. These white clouds left in the sky by aircraft may add to climate change <a href=\\"https://www.faa.gov/sites/faa.gov/files/regulations_policies/policy_guidance/envir_policy/contrails.pdf\\">if they persist</a> long enough."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;There are still doubts about the climate impact of hydrogen aviation,&rdquo; said Matteo Mirolo, a sustainable aviation expert at Breakthrough Energy, an organization founded by <a href=\\"https://www.weforum.org/organizations/zeroavia/\\">Bill Gates that is also investing</a> in developing hydrogen aircraft."},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"&ldquo;We still don&rsquo;t know exactly the non-CO2 impact of hydrogen,&rdquo; said Mirolo, adding that hydrogen-powered aircraft would, however, have &ldquo;a positive impact, reducing pollution levels compared to fossil kerosene-powered aircraft, including particulate matter.&rdquo;"},{"tag":"p","type":"paragraph","attributes":{},"content":"T&amp;E&rsquo;s L&oacute;pez de la Osa argues that cleaner-burning hydrogen engines mean contrails are likely to be short-lived. &ldquo;Hydrogen combustion